Class LockingSetDecorator<E>

java.lang.Object

E -
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, Set<E>
public class LockingSetDecorator<E>
extends SetDecorator<E>

SetDecorator which uses a Lock to synchronize all of its methods. The iterator() method will return a locked Iterator which uses the same Lock instance.

Author:
Omnaest
See Also:
SetUtils.locked(Set, Lock), SetUtils.lockedByReentrantLock(Set), Serialized Form
